11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6-187E of Title 70, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 A. The Commission for Educational Quality and Accountability
16 shall establish student teaching requirements for teacher candidates
17 who are enrolled in an educator preparation program accredited by
18 the Commission. The requirements shall include:
19 1. Completion of a minimum number of weeks of field experience;
20 or
21 2. Completion of a qualified job-embedded, competency-based
22 teacher registered apprenticeship program. For the purposes of this
23 section, “teacher registered apprenticeship program” means a
